        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/pakistan-claims-indian-jet-wreckage.png" alt="Troops stand next to what Pakistan says is the wreckage of an Indian fighter jet its military shot down" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Troops stand next to what Pakistan says is the wreckage of an Indian fighter jet its military shot down. Credits: STRINGER / AFP/ Getty Images</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          The Indian Army launched a series of precision strikes targeting the terror infrastructure of Pakistan-Occupied Kashmir and Pakistan. In a statement, they confirmed that no Pakistani military facilities have been targeted. The strikes, carried out under '<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-8-may-25-spotlight-h1-1-operation-sindoor?source=website" target="_blank">Operation Sindoor</a>', targeted 21 locations including Sawai Nala, and Syed Na Bilal, Maskar-e-Aqsa.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         Following the operations, the Union Government called for an all-party meeting to brief them about the operation. While the fact-check unit of India's Press Information Bureau (PIB) dismissed a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-8-may-25-spotlight-h1-2-fake-claim?source=website" target="_blank">fake claim</a> that Pakistan had carried out strikes on a military base in Amritsar, India, on the ground reports mention â€œa fireball-like projectile and a loud blast" heard over the city. Amid heightened tensions, NSA Ajit Doval spoke to his Pakistani counterpart, Lieutenant General Asim Malik, to de-escalate the situation.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;filter:blur(5px);">
          Pakistani troops continued cross-border shelling along the Line of Control (LoC) in Kupwara district of Jammu and Kashmir. Officials confirmed civilian deaths in the Karnah region. Pakistan's Defence Minister also failed to justify the claim of downing Indian jets.
         </p>
        
        
